16/04/2008
NOVI SAD, Serbia -- One football fan was killed and four were injured, one seriously, in a clash between fans of Vojvodina Novi Sad and Partizan Belgrade late Monday (April 14th) in Novi Sad. 
Police confirmed that a Vojvodina fan was shot dead in the melee. 
Some local media are reporting that the fight was prearranged on the internet. 
Vojvodina and Partizan fans had already clashed at the weekend, following a first-division match between the two clubs. 
(B92, RTS, Tanjug, Javno.com, DPA - 15/04/08)
